Template: scramlkb/grub
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Enable Scramlkb for cryptsetup prompt at boot time?
 Enabling Scramlkb as a password agent for cryptsetup at boot requires
 an appropriate kernel command line option. This can be configured
 by setting GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="scramlkb=1" in /etc/default/grub
 and running grub-update.
 .
 If you accept here, these actions will be performed automatically and
 Scramlkb will be enabled at next boot.
